items.abstract: <jats:p>The aim of presented work was to analyze the impact of particular polymorphic changes in the promoter regions of the -1607 1G/2G<jats:italic>MMP1</jats:italic>, -1562 C/T<jats:italic>MMP9</jats:italic>, -82 A/G<jats:italic>MMP12</jats:italic>, -511 C/T<jats:italic>IL-1<jats:italic>β</jats:italic></jats:italic>, and 372 T/C<jats:italic>TIMP1</jats:italic>genes on their expression level in POAG patients. Blood and aqueous humor samples acquired from 50 patients with POAG and 50 control subjects were used for QPCR and protein levels analysis by ELISA.<jats:italic>In vivo</jats:italic>promoter activity assays were carried on HTM cells using dual luciferase assay. All studied subjects underwent ophthalmic examination, including BCVA, intraocular pressure, slit-lamp examination, gonioscopy, HRT, and OCT scans. Patients with POAG are characterized by an increased mRNA expression of<jats:italic>MMP1</jats:italic>,<jats:italic>MMP9</jats:italic>,<jats:italic>MMP12</jats:italic>, and<jats:italic>IL-1<jats:italic>β</jats:italic></jats:italic>genes as compared to the control group (<mml:math xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" id="M2"><mml:mi>P</mml:mi><mml:mo><</mml:mo><mml:mn fontstyle="italic">0.001</mml:mn></mml:math>). Aqueous humor acquired from patients with POAG displayed increased protein expression of MMP1, MMP9, MMP12, and IL-1<jats:italic><jats:italic>β</jats:italic></jats:italic>compared to the control group (<mml:math xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" id="M3"><mml:mi>P</mml:mi><mml:mo><</mml:mo><mml:mn fontstyle="italic">0.001</mml:mn></mml:math>). Allele -1607 1G of<jats:italic>MMP1</jats:italic>gene possesses only 42,91% of the -1607 2G allele transcriptional activity and allele -1562 C of<jats:italic>MMP9</jats:italic>gene possesses only 21,86% of the -1562 T allele. Increased expression levels of metalloproteinases can be considered as a risk factor for the development of POAG.</jats:p>
